{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"5221f59e75ea9db114593bbdfb180b7354aef9ed"},"timestamp":1521503371,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUzMDY2Nzg3NTY=","github-url":"https://github.com/DFHack/dfhack/issues/1243","origin":"github"},"title":"DigType places designations on inappropriate tiles","message":"Using the \"digtype\" command blindly places Dig designations on all tiles which coincide with a `block_square_event_mineralst` having the same vein material, without first checking that the tile type's material is MINERAL. As a result, it places dig designations in tiles that have been overwritten by map features - open space, subterranean trees, raw adamantine, semi-molten rock, and slade (which can go all the way down to the very bottom of the map and lead to bug #1240).","files":null}]}